    "title": "Manufacturing Engineer - Indian Oil Corporation - Freshers Welcome",
    "description": "Indian Oil Corporation is actively seeking a talented and motivated Manufacturing Engineer to join our dynamic team in Nagpur. This is an excellent opportunity for professionals who are passionate about making a real impact in a fast-growing organization.\n\nAbout Indian Oil Corporation:\nIndian Oil Corporation is a leading organization in the On-site sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Implement 5S, Kaizen, and Six Sigma practices on the shop floor\n• Conduct root cause analysis for quality rejections and defects\n• Monitor equipment performance and coordinate preventive maintenance\n• Coordinate with design and engineering teams on product improvements\n• Ensure compliance with safety regulations and factory acts\n• Manage supplier quality audits and vendor development\n• Implement lean manufacturing and continuous improvement initiatives\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• Master's degree preferred\n• 0-1 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in ISO 9001\n• Proficiency in FMEA\n• Proficiency in APQP\n• Proficiency in Six Sigma\n• Proficiency in Root Cause Analysis\n• Proficiency in PPAP\n• Proficiency in TPM\n• Proficiency in Lean Manufacturing\n\nWork Mode: On-site - Work from our office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Annual paid leaves and casual leaves\n• Mobile and internet reimbursement\n• Employee stock options (ESOPs) for eligible roles\n• Provident Fund and Gratuity as per company policy\n• Transportation and conveyance allowance\n• Flexible working hours\n• Salary Range: 2.5 LPA - 6 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Nagpur, Maharashtra, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Indian Oil Corporation!",
